];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="AV Ninjas"
  description="We provide sound, video, and lighting for meetings and events."
>
  <a href="#main" class="skip-link">Skip to content</a>
  <!-- §16 / B2 / B7: no-JS fallback — pre-draw every highlight marker so they are
       visible without scripts (the JS path animates them on scroll-into-view). -->
  <noscript>
    <style>
      .highlight-seg,
      .highlight-static,
      .nfb-seg { background-size: 100% 88% !important; transition: none !important; }
      /* v05: no-JS — The Ninjas points are shown immediately (no fade). */
      .ninjas-points li { opacity: 1 !important; transform: none !important; transition: none !important; }
    </style>
  </noscript>
  <SiteHeader />

  <main id="main">
    <!-- ============================================================
         BAND 1 — OPEN. Hero, canvas, standalone. (sweep §B.1)
         ============================================================ -->

    <!-- ============ 1. HERO (canvas, full viewport on load) ============ -->
    <!-- §9: the hero fills the ENTIRE viewport on first paint, every device.
         100dvh so mobile browser chrome can't break it. Left text block + right
         dominant image (the hero is the one "special" archetype — left, not
         centered, per sweep §A.3 row 1). -->
    <section class="hero-section" id="hero" aria-label="Hero">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <h1 class="display">Hey! We're the AV Ninjas.</h1>
          <!-- B3 (round-5): accent the three service words. Hero is a LIGHT ground →
               --color-accent (#1D4ED8), the light-voice accent (Iris flag). -->
          <!-- The trailing comma/space stays INSIDE each accent span so the decoded
               copy keeps "sound, video, and lighting" contiguous (the fidelity
               check collapses whitespace but each tag boundary injects a space —
               keeping punctuation in-span avoids a stray space before the comma).
               Only the words are visibly colored; "color" on a comma is invisible. -->
          <p class="lead">We provide <span class="svc-accent">sound, </span><span class="svc-accent">video, </span>and <span class="svc-accent">lighting</span> for meetings and events.</p>
          <p class="lead">
            We work directly with
            <!-- MOTION MOMENT 1 of 3: the one-and-only animated highlight (GL-003 §6).
                 B2 (round-5): ONE CONTINUOUS sweep — segment 1 draws, then segment 2
                 draws as a single flowing draw (line 1 → line 2, NOT parallel). The
                 phrase is split at its natural wrap so each visual line is its own
                 sequenced segment; the verbatim copy is unchanged (the split is only
                 between two highlight spans, no characters added/removed). Slowed
                 overall via --motion-hero-sweep. -->
            <span class="highlight-sweep"
              ><span class="highlight-seg highlight-seg--1">EA's, Execs, Agencies and Event</span> <span class="highlight-seg highlight-seg--2">Planners</span></span>
            - and our whole business built around making it easy!
          </p>
          <p class="hero-kicker">Skip the headaches. Go Direct!</p>
          <div class="btn-row">
            <!-- [PENDING BEN: CTA destination — Calendly/contact not wired (Mack's layer)] -->
            <!-- Primary "Let's Talk" = the gradient POP moment (GL-003 §2 use #1) -->
            <a href="#" class="btn btn--gradient" data-pending="cta-destination">Let's Talk!</a>
            <a href="#audiences" class="btn btn--secondary">Learn More</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <Image
          class="img-real hero-img"
          src={heroTrioImg}
          alt={heroTrioAlt}
          widths={[480, 768, 1100, 1376]}
          sizes="(min-width: 920px) 56vw, 100vw"
          loading="eager"
          fetchpriority="high"
        />
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================
         BAND A — "Who you are / what you face." Audiences → Ticker →
         Attention → Sound Dramatic. Opens DARK (Audiences image-wall), then
         dark-fades up to canvas/cream. Earned dark moment: Audiences. (§B.1)
         ============================================================ -->

    <!-- FULL-BLEED #1 (sweep §C) — Audiences band opener. The cinematic entry
         into "who you are": a wide ballroom on dark, ink scrim, centered head +
         the three locked labels sit BELOW on the dark band. -->
    <section class="section section--roomy section--dark band-open" id="audiences" data-dark-fade aria-label="Audiences">
      <figure class="fullbleed audiences-bleed">
        <Image
          class="fullbleed__img"
          src={audInPersonImg}
          alt={audInPersonAlt}
          widths={[768, 1280, 1920]}
          sizes="100vw"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <div class="fullbleed__scrim"></div>
        <div class="fullbleed__inner">
          <div class="container">
            <h2 class="sec-head sec-head--onbleed">Audiences of Every Shape and Size</h2>
          </div>
        </div>
      </figure>

      <div class="container">
        <!-- Heading↔picture correspondence (Ben, from Winona's site): each label
             is LOCKED to its image as a caption. DOM order + aria-hidden middots
             reconstruct the canonical "In Person · Hybrid · All Virtual" string
             for copy fidelity, while each label sits with its own picture.
             §11: each card carries a "Learn More" button that expands the panel
             to a FULL-VIEWPORT takeover (the overlay below). -->
        <!-- Canonical "In Person · Hybrid · All Virtual" string, kept contiguous
             (sr-only) for copy fidelity — the visible labels are split across the
             three cards (each with its own Learn More button), which would
             otherwise break the contiguous run. -->
        <p class="sr-only">In Person · Hybrid · All Virtual</p>
        <ul class="audiences-grid" aria-label="In Person, Hybrid, All Virtual">
          {audiences.map((aud, i) => (
            <>
              {i > 0 && <li class="aud-sep" aria-hidden="true">·</li>}
              <li class="aud-card">
                <Image
                  class="img-real aud-img"
                  src={aud.img}
                  alt={aud.alt}
                  widths={[320, 480, 928, 1152]}
                  sizes="(min-width: 768px) 30vw, 90vw"
                  loading="lazy"
                />
                <span class="aud-label">{aud.label}</span>
                <button
                  type="button"
                  class="aud-more"
                  data-aud-open={aud.id}
                  aria-haspopup="dialog"
                >
                  Learn More
                  <span class="sr-only"> about {aud.label} events</span>
                </button>
              </li>
            </>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- §11: full-viewport takeover panels. One <dialog>-pattern overlay per
           audience; clicking a card's "Learn More" expands its black frame to
           fill the entire viewport. Esc / close / backdrop collapses it. Focus
           is trapped while open; aria-modal + labelledby for SR users. The
           panels are hidden by default and revealed by the script (progressive
           enhancement — with no JS the cards still link nowhere harmful). -->
      {audiences.map((aud) => (
        <div
          class="aud-takeover"
          id={`aud-panel-${aud.id}`}
          data-aud-panel={aud.id}
          role="dialog"
          aria-modal="true"
          aria-labelledby={`aud-panel-${aud.id}-title`}
          hidden
        >
          <Image
            class="aud-takeover__img"
            src={aud.img}
            alt={aud.alt}
            widths={[768, 1280, 1920]}
            sizes="100vw"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <div class="aud-takeover__scrim"></div>
          <button type="button" class="aud-takeover__close" data-aud-close aria-label="Close">
            <span aria-hidden="true">×</span>
          </button>
          <div class="aud-takeover__inner">
            <p class="aud-takeover__eyebrow">Audiences of Every Shape and Size</p>
            <h3 class="aud-takeover__title" id={`aud-panel-${aud.id}-title`}>{aud.label}</h3>
            <p class="aud-takeover__support">{aud.support}</p>
            {aud.body.split("\n\n").map((para) => <p class="aud-takeover__body">{para}</p>)}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}

      <!-- 3. EVENT-TYPES TICKER (marquee) — full-width band, part of Band A. -->
      <div class="audiences-ticker">
        <Marquee items={marqueeItems} />
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============ 4. ATTENTION (canvas — SPLIT, head CENTERED) ============ -->
    <!-- Band A continues on light after the dark-fade up. SPLIT archetype:
         image-left + verb list right, shared top/bottom edge. -->
    <section class="section band-tight attention-section" id="attention" aria-label="Attention">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="sec-head">With Live Events, Attention is the Currency</h2>
        <div class="split split--img-left attention-split">
          <div class="split__media attention-media">
            <!-- §13: the REAL back-logo composite (Mack v4-composited). -->
            <Image
              class="img-real"
              src={attentionImg}
              alt={audHybridAlt}
              widths={[480, 768, 928]}
              sizes="(min-width: 920px) 42vw, 100vw"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="split__copy">
            <p class="lead">There are countless reasons to gather people together into a space...</p>
            <!-- iconed verb quartet — monochrome ink, copy verbatim.
                 B4 (round-5): removed the inter-item middot separators. They were
                 rendering inconsistently (stray dots ahead of "motivate" and
                 "strategize" where the row wrapped) — the icons already delimit the
                 items, so every verb now reads identically (icon + verb, no dot). -->
            <ul class="verb-row" aria-label="to inspire, to motivate, to inform, to strategize">
              <li><Icon name="attention-inspire" size={36} /><span>to inspire</span></li>
              <li><Icon name="attention-motivate" size={36} /><span>to motivate</span></li>
              <li><Icon name="attention-inform" size={36} /><span>to inform</span></li>
              <li><Icon name="attention-strategize" size={36} /><span>to strategize</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============ 5. SOUND DRAMATIC (cream — SPLIT img-left, head CENTERED) ============ -->
    <section class="section section--cream band-tight" id="sound-dramatic" aria-label="Sound Dramatic">
      <div class="container">
        <!-- §14: headline on ONE line (no wrap). -->
        <h2 class="sec-head sound-head">Sound Dramatic? Consider this...</h2>
        <div class="split split--img-left sound-split">
          <!-- MOTION MOMENT 2 of 3 (§10): a real VIDEO of a phone buzzing on the
               banquet table. No synthetic screen, no notification overlay — the
               base media simply IS the buzz. Playback starts on scroll-into-view
               (IntersectionObserver below) so the phone "wakes up as you reach it";
               prefers-reduced-motion gets the poster still only, never autoplay.
               Assets (Mack) drop into public/media/ at the exact paths below. -->
          <div class="split__media phone-stage" id="phone-moment">
            <video
              class="phone-video"
              src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}media/phone-buzz.mp4`}
              poster={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}media/phone-buzz-poster.jpg`}
              muted
              loop
              playsinline
              preload="metadata"
              aria-label="A smartphone lying face-up on a banquet table during a live ballroom event buzzes with an incoming notification, the engaged crowd and stage beyond."
            >
              <source src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}media/phone-buzz.webm`} type="video/webm" />
              <source src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}media/phone-buzz.mp4`} type="video/mp4" />
            </video>
          </div>
          <div class="split__copy">
            <p>
              According to one study, the AVERAGE smartphone user sees $60 of targeted
              advertising per day. For your audience that number could easily be 5-10x+!!!
            </p>

            <div class="dramatic-block">
              <h3 class="subhead">The Invisible Army</h3>
              <p>
                Event organizers are quite literally sparring with an army of the
                highest-paid social engineers in the world to get - and keep - their
                audience's attention. Not one of us is immune because the hooks are primal.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="dramatic-block">
              <h3 class="subhead">The Stakes have Never Been Higher!</h3>
              <p>
                We all know how this goes. At the first hint of dead air, fuzzy audio,
                or hard-to-read slides, the first phone comes out, then the second..
              </p>
              <p>Stream dropped for 10 minutes plus? There went 2/3 of your virtual participants... Yikes!</p>
              <p>
                One thing is for sure: No one has ever gone to the effort of booking a
                venue, lining up speakers, building an itinerary, etc to fill a room full
                of people just so they can all sit in the same place just to doom scroll.
              </p>
              <p>AV can elevate your event or sink it like a torpedo.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

